  <description type="morphology">Stems erect, 20–80(–120) cm. Cauline leaf blades lanceolate to linear, reduced distally (becoming bractlike near heads), margins usually serrate apically, rarely entire. Peduncles stipitate-glandular, sometimes hispid as well. Involucres campanulate, (3.5–)5–8(–10) mm diam. Ray florets (10–)13–21(–29); corolla laminae 6–12 mm. Disc florets (20–)33–70(–108). 2n = 10, 12, 14.</description>
  <description type="distribution">sc United States</description>
